task.summary: Reads and prints lines from the file, need to split each line as values for AthleteInfo instances and save those instances in AthleteInfoList. AthleteInfoList will most likely be used as input for calculations, but we'll see.

Reads and splits lines from file into values for AthleteInfo variables. Currently does NOT save AthleteInfo instances in AthleteInfoList. Try...catch added for when the line might be missing info. Need to also add exceptions for when the info is in the wrong format.
Adds instances of AthleteInfo to AthleteInfoList. Exceptions will be dealt with when the code is mostly done. Next step is a class for the calculations.

Starting work on Calculations class. Added an integer variable to AthleteInfo for total points. Further clarification of AthleteInfo variables. Corrected some test names. Decided to use longer names for variables because the names started to get silly.

Finished initial version of Calculations class. Next, need to test said class. Had accidentally forgotten to change get methods to return int for jumps - remedied that issue. Changed test names to match longer variable names.

Added test for Calculations class (once again, all test will be in a separate test folder when I'm done). Next, need to add sorting for results (easy enough, but maybe do something more interesting/potentially faster than bubble sort?) and then make a printer class.
Made a bogosort version just to try it and it actually works, but I also found out about Collections.sort(), so I'll do that. Bogosort version is going in a separate branch.

Removed FileNotFound exceptions - methods that I use to read the file just don't throw it.
